expect.help:
⊙`Snap To Road`: Takes up to 100 GPS points collected along a route, and returns a similar set of data, with the points snapped to the most likely roads the vehicle was traveling along.
⊙`Nearest Roads`: Takes up to 100 independent coordinates, and returns the closest road segment for each point.
⊙`Speed Limits`: Returns the posted speed limit for a given road segment. The Speed Limit service is available to all customers with an Asset Tracking license. For "Google Maps Platform Premium Plan" customers who transitioned to pay-as-you-go pricing, the feature remains active.
